<item>
            <title>[LU-12993] Add missing licensing information to specfile</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12993</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Lustre specfile included in Lustre source code specify Lustre licensing information, GPL.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lustre is licensed partially under GPLv2 and partially under LGPLv2.1 for &lt;tt&gt;liblustreapi&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The specfile should be adapted to include both license files and both license names.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Following Fedora Packaging Guidelines, the license should be set as&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;GPLv2 and LGPLv2.1&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The LGPLv2.1 license file is available in lustre/utils directory but should be included as %doc likewise the GPL license file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the RPM specfile authorizes that, only the part containing the &lt;tt&gt;liblustreapi&lt;/tt&gt; should have the 2 licences. If not possible, better to set that globally.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
